text: Serra do Navio (), (Mountain range of the Ship) is a municipality located in the center of the state of Amapá in Brazil. Its population is 4,938 (2015 est.) and its area is 7,713 km². The municipality contains 7.83% of the Amapá State Forest, a sustainable use conservation unit established in 2006. ==Climate== ==References== Category:Municipalities in Amapá
